@@TJvXMLDatabase
<TITLEIMG TJvXMLDatabase>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.Internet.ConvertersAndParsers.XML,JVCL.DBAware
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  A component to access the content of an XML file using SQL like syntax.
Description
  TJvXMLDatabase is a component to retrieve data from an XML file using SQL like syntax. Specify the
  SQL string by assigning to the Query property. This component also has limited support for update
  statements.
Note
  * All columns in the WHERE clause must be part of the SELECT clause as well
  * WHERE conditions must be enclosed in parenthesizes (i.e WHERE (Col1=5) AND Col2='Noodles')
  * Update statements are limited to simple operations (i.e SET Col1 = Col1 + 1, Col2 = 'FooBar')

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXMLDatabase.Query
Summary
  Specifies the SQL like string to use to retrieve data from the XML file.
Description
  Call Query to send an SQL statement to the XML file or files and optionally retrieve any results
Parameters
  AQuery - The SQL string to send to the XML file or files.
Return value
  A TJvXMLQuery instance that describes any returned values. Use the return value to iterate over all
  found nodes.
See Also
  TJvXMLQuery

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXMLDatabase.SaveTables
Summary
  Saves changes made to all loaded tables (XML files).
Description
  Call SaveTables to save modifications done to any loaded table. Tables are loaded as required by
  queries. If your queries makes changes to the loaded XML files (using update statements like SET),
  the changes will not be saved back to file unless SaveTables is called.
See Also
  TJvXMLDatabase.Query

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXMLDatabase.TablesPath
Summary
  Specifies where XML files are located.
Description
  Use TablePath to specify the path to the data (XML) files. This path is used in conjuction with
  filenames in the SQL statement sent in Query to determine what file or files to read from. For
  example, if TablePath is set to 'C:\\temp\\tables' and Query contains 'SELECT * FROM data1.xml', the
  component will look for the file C:\\temp\\tables\\data1.xml.
See Also
  TJvXMLDatabase.Query

